cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

This paper deals with Relation Extraction (RE) using multiple knowledge bases and constructing a taxonomical hierarchy of canonicalized relations. The primary focus is on entity types such as person, organization, and location. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category as it deals with natural language processing and information retrieval. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper uses multiple resources to extract relations. cs.DB (Databases) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with knowledge bases such as Wikidata and DBpedia. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also possible sub-categories as the paper uses data-driven methods to extract and combine relations.
